A marine terrace is a type of terrace and also a type of something that is at least located in some marine water body. It is defined as a terrace which is located in a marine water body. Furthermore, marine terrace has narrow synonyms such as bench and bench (seafloor), and it has a related synonym, which is marine bench.
Meander neck is a type of landform and is specifically the narrowest part of a meander, defined as a landform which is at least part of some meander.

Blanket bog is a type of peatland characterized by a unique form of development that is largely independent of basins or topographical features where water collects; instead, it spreads across the landscape akin to a blanket. The development of peat in blanket bogs is facilitated by a constant supply of water from rainfall, which ensures the ground remains waterlogged. These bogs are ombrotrophic or rain-fed, leading to their pH ranging between 3.5 and 4.2. Blanket bog is broadly synonymous with the term wetland.

A pond bed is a type of submerged bed and is something that is at least adjacent to some pond. It is defined as the ground surface that lies beneath a pond. Additionally, pond bed has an exact synonym: pond bottom.

A reservoir bed is a type of submerged bed and is also a type of structure that is at least adjacent to some reservoir. It is defined as the ground surface that lies beneath a reservoir and is exactly synonymous with reservoir bottom.
A crater is a type of depressed landform, which is defined as a generally circular saucer or bowl-shaped depression caused by explosive action. Moreover, it has an exact synonym, CRATER.

A road cut is defined as a cut to provide passage for a road. It is the same as something that is both an intersection of something that cuts and something that at least has part of some road. Additionally, a road cut is a type of cut and also a type of something that at least has part of some road.
Hummock is a type of elevated and surface landform with the definition being a patch of ground, distinct from and slightly above the surrounding plain or wetland, and often occurs in groups.

A lost stream is a type of stream defined as a surface stream that disappears into an underground channel or dries up in an arid area. It is broadly synonymous with lost river, lost watercourse, and stream, but it also specifically has a narrow synonym: lost river.

Ditch mouth shares the same characteristics as both a type of mouth and something that is at least part of a ditch. It specifically refers to the exit or point of discharge of a ditch, encapsulating its definition.
An agricultural terrace is a type of agricultural ecosystem and a type of terrace. It is defined as a terrace which is used for agricultural activities.

A landslide is a type of surface landform, which is also a physiographic feature, and has broad synonyms such as landslip, slide, and slide (natural). It is a formation that occurs as a result of a landslide process and is primarily composed of materials such as scree, rock, soil, sediment, mud, and sand. Furthermore, a landslide is defined as a mound of earth material at the base of a slope, including the associated scoured area.

Rockfall is a type of landslide and is primarily composed of rock. It is defined as an irregular mass of fallen rock at the base of a cliff or steep slope. This phenomenon occurs adjacent to areas that are a union of cliffs and slopes, and it is formed as a result of the rockslide process.
A canal tunnel is a type of man-made tunnel defined as a tunnel through which a canal passes. It is broadly synonymous with the term "tunnel."

A cutoff is a type of channel of a watercourse, defined as a channel formed as a result of a stream cutting through a meander neck. It is also known by its exact synonyms: cut off, cutoff (hydrographic), and cuttoff.

An abandoned watercourse is a type of landform categorized both as a depressed and a surface landform. It is defined as a former stream or distributary that no longer carries flowing water, yet remains evident due to the presence of lakes, wetlands, topographic, or vegetation patterns.
A canalized stream is a type of stream that has been substantially ditched, diked, or straightened. It is broadly synonymous with a canal and exactly synonymous with a canalised stream.

Cliff cleft is a type of surface landform and is considered a part of some cliffs. It is defined as a deep narrow slot, notch, or groove in a cliff. Additionally, "cleft" is a related synonym to cliff cleft.
Interfluve is a type of elevated and surface landform that is defined as a relatively undissected upland between adjacent stream valleys. Additionally, interfluve has a broad synonym: plain.

An ice cap ridge is defined as a linear elevation on an icecap, which is the same as the intersection of a ridge and a feature that is at least partially part of an ice cap. This indicates that an ice cap ridge is a specific type of ridge and also belongs to entities that are partially part of an ice cap. It is broadly synonymous with "ridge" and has an exact synonym "icecap reach."

A beach ridge is identical to an entity that is the intersection of a ridge and an entity that is at least adjacent to a beach. It is a type of ridge and also a type of entity that is at least adjacent to a beach. Furthermore, a beach ridge is defined as a ridge of sand just inland and parallel to the beach, usually in series.

An apron is defined as a type of slope that is a gentle slope, with a generally smooth surface, particularly found around groups of islands and seamounts. It has related synonyms including apron (geological), archipelago apron, and undersea apron.

Ice cap depression is a type of depressed landform, surface landform, and something that is at least part of some ice cap. It is defined as a depression which is part of an ice cap. Additionally, ice cap depression has both an exact synonym and a related synonym as icecap depression.

An intermittent saline evaporation pond is a type of container for an intermittent pond and is involved in a process that includes both the water accumulation process and involves saline evaporation ponds which have the quality of being discontinuous. Furthermore, "lake" is considered a broad synonym for intermittent saline evaporation pond, while "intermittent salt pond" is an exact synonym.

Landfill is a type of landform, specifically a depressed and surface landform, defined as a depression which contains objects and materials discarded by humans or their technologies. It has several exact synonyms, including Deponie, discarica, garbage dump, rubbish dump, vertedero, and 垃圾掩埋場. Additionally, landfill has a related synonym, disposal site.

A riverine pothole is a type of depressed and surface landform that is part of, or intersects with, a watercourse and the solid surface layer, possessing a smooth quality. It is characterized by shapes that include a union of cylindrical, U-shaped, and tubular forms and is primarily composed of rock. Broad synonyms for a riverine pothole include churn hole, evorsion, kettle, pot, and rock mill. Exact synonyms are eddy mill, giant's kettle, kolk, stream kettle, and swirlhole.
A weir is a type of dam and is defined as a low obstruction built across the path of a stream to raise its level.

Moatan is a type of depressed landform and also a type of entity that is at least adjacent to some hydrographic feature. It is defined as an annular depression that may not be continuous, located at the base of many seamounts, islands, and other isolated elevations.

A boulder field is a type of elevated and surface landform, characterized by being something that at least has a part comprising some boulders. It is defined as a high altitude or high latitude bare, flat area covered with large angular rocks.

Arrugado is a type of surface landform and also a type of something that is at least part of or adjacent to some sea floor and marine water body, respectively. It is defined as an undersea area of subdued corrugations.

A geographic sill is a type of depressed landform and is defined as the low part of a gap or saddle separating basins. It is broadly synonymous with the term "sill" and has related synonyms including "gap" and "sill (physiographic)."

A brackish lake is a type of saline lake and also a type of brackish water body. It is defined as a lake which is primarily composed of brackish water, having a higher salinity than fresh water but a lower salinity than marine water.

A brackish pond is both a type of pond and a type of brackish water body, essentially defined as a pond primarily composed of brackish water. This definition aligns with the concept that a brackish pond is the same as something that represents the intersection between a pond and a water body that is at least primarily composed of brackish water.

Kame is identified as a type of elevated and surface landform. It is distinguished by being at least partly composed of an intersection between layers and a mixture primarily of sand and gravel. Additionally, a kame is characterized by having a part that is an intersection of both sand and gravel, and possesses stratified qualities. A kame is defined as an irregularly shaped hill or mound that consists of sorted or stratified sand and gravel deposited in contact with glacial ice. This formation can have an irregular shape and is often found in association with kettles, leading to the term "kame and kettle topography." When the ice retreats further, the delta kame may collapse. Kame terraces, which are deposits of meltwater streams flowing between the ice and the adjacent valley side, are commonly located along the sides of a glacial valley. Furthermore, kame is broadly synonymous with terms like mount and ridge.

Swale is a type of depressed and surface landform, defined as a depression which comprises a low tract of land, especially when moist or marshy. Additionally, swale is synonymously related to a trough.

Leat is a type of artificial channel with a specific definition. It is a man-made watercourse, or makeshift aqueduct, often an artificial channel which supplies water to a watermill or its mill pond, collecting water from upstream of the mill so that the natural level of the driving water is above the level of the stream at the mill. Alternatively, it may deliver water for mineral washing and concentration, irrigation, or to a dye works. Additionally, leat has an exact synonym, which is lete.

Shingle beach is a type of beach and is also known as a pebble beach. It is characterized by being a beach that is armored with pebbles or small to medium-sized cobbles. Furthermore, a shingle beach is a type of environment that includes at least some part consisting of pebbles.

Lake sediment is a type of sediment that is found at least adjacent to some lake and is an output of sedimentation in a water body. It is defined as sediment which covers the bottom of a lake, mainly comprised of clastic material (sediment of clay, silt, and sand sizes), organic debris, chemical precipitates, or combinations of these. Moreover, lake sediment has a related synonym, SedimentLayer.

A waterhole is a type of pond and is defined as a pond, often temporary or seasonal, used as a drinking place by mammals and birds. It is exactly synonymous with "water hole" and also has "water hole" and "waterhole" as related synonyms.

A gravel field is a type of field that is composed primarily of gravel. It is defined as a field which is primarily made up of gravel. Additionally, "gravel field area" is a related synonym for gravel field.

A container of an intermittent water body is recognized as a type of depressed landform and also as a type of surface landform. It falls under the category of entities that at least contain a process intersecting water accumulation and processes that have a discontinuous quality. This entity is defined as a depression that is periodically filled with water when the water supply exceeds evapotranspiration and bed seepage. Furthermore, it is exactly synonymous with both an intermittent body of water and an intermittent water body.

A range of seamounts is a type of mountain range that is characterized by being at least partially surrounded by a body of water that is either an ocean, a sea, or a combination of both. This range is specifically located in marine water bodies and includes at least a portion that consists of seamounts. It is defined as a mountain range submerged under a marine water body. Additionally, a range of seamounts is associated with several synonyms, including cordillera, seamount chain, seamount group, seamount range, undersea cordillera, undersea mountain chain, and undersea range.

An endorheic basin is a type of drainage basin defined as a drainage basin from which there is no outflow of water, either on the surface as rivers or underground by flow or diffusion through rock or permeable material. Furthermore, it is related to the synonyms "closed basin" and "terminal basin."

Talik is a type of part of a landmass and a type of surface landform. It is also described as a complement of permafrost and is at least partially surrounded by permafrost. The definition of talik is an area of unfrozen ground surrounded by permafrost. Additionally, it has an exact synonym, Talik.
A multipurpose dam is a type of dam that is constructed for more than one purpose.

A saddle dam is a type of dam with the definition as an auxiliary dam constructed to confine the reservoir created by a primary dam. This construction is either to permit a higher water elevation and storage or to limit the extent of a reservoir for increased efficiency.
A check dam is a type of dam designed to reduce flow velocity and control soil erosion.
A wing dam is a type of dam that is defined as a dam that only partly restricts a waterway, creating a faster channel that resists the accumulation of sediment.
